briefdescription.para: Gives the primary type of Abstract.

detaileddescription.para:
In the program this function is very often called. It allows different functions to know what type of expr they are manipulating (single number, scalar function with one argument, with multiple argumments, a Vector, etc) in order to do special treatments or simplifications.
type (a non memorized integer corresponding to the type of abstract)

briefdescription.para: Returns the numerical factor of the expression, i.e. returns C if the expression if of the form C*x (x having a numerical factor equal to 1), and return 1 else.

simplesect.para: This function returns the factor in an Expression (then of Numerical type).
The numerical factor in front of the expression.

briefdescription.para: This function returns the same expression as *this but amputated of its numerical factor. Example: (4*cos(x) -> cos(x)).

simplesect.para: The term without numerical factor corresponding to *this.

briefdescription.para: Evaluates the argument in the complex plane of the Abstract and returns it.

simplesect.para: The argument part of the Abstract.

briefdescription.para: Check recursively if the expression depends on expr.

simplesect.para: True if a dependency in expr is found.

briefdescription.para: Check recursively if expr is present in the expression.
Abstract class from which derive numerical types, i.e. Float, Integer, IntFraction.
